h3cE1.description: This MIB provides E1 interface information that are excluded by RFC 1213 and RFC 2233

e1InterfaceStatusTable.name: e1InterfaceStatusTable
e1InterfaceStatusTable.description: This table contains E1 interface packet statistics

e1InterfaceStatusEntry.name: e1InterfaceStatusEntry
e1InterfaceStatusEntry.description: This entry contains E1 interface packet statistics. The index of this Entry is ifIndex defined in ifTable of RFC1213-MIB

e1InterfaceInErrs.name: e1InterfaceInErrs
e1InterfaceInErrs.description: The total number of error received on this interface

e1InterfaceInRuntsErrs.name: e1InterfaceInRuntsErrs

e1InterfaceInGiantsErrs.name: e1InterfaceInGiantsErrs
e1InterfaceInGiantsErrs.description: The number of Giants Error(too long packet) received on this interface

e1InterfaceInCrcErrs.name: e1InterfaceInCrcErrs
e1InterfaceInCrcErrs.description: The number of CRC Error received on this interface

e1InterfaceInAlignErrs.name: e1InterfaceInAlignErrs

e1InterfaceInOverRunsErrs.name: e1InterfaceInOverRunsErrs

e1InterfaceInDribblesErrs.name: e1InterfaceInDribblesErrs

e1InterfaceInAbortedSeqErrs.name: e1InterfaceInAbortedSeqErrs
e1InterfaceInAbortedSeqErrs.description: The number of AbortedSeq Error received on this interface

e1InterfaceInNoBufferErrs.name: e1InterfaceInNoBufferErrs

h3ce1Table.name: h3ce1Table
h3ce1Table.description: A list of E1 interface entries.

h3ce1Entry.name: h3ce1Entry
h3ce1Entry.description: This entry contains E1 interface management information.

H3cE1TimeSlot.name: H3cE1TimeSlot
H3cE1TimeSlot.description: Each octet within this value specifies a set of time slots, with the first octet specifying time slot 1 through 8, the second octet specifying time slots 9 through 16, etc. Within each octet, the most significant bit represents the highest numbered time slot, and the least significant bit represents the lowest numbered time slot. Thus, each time slot of the E1 is represented by a single bit within the value of this object. If that bit has a value of '1' then that time slot is included in the set of time slots; the time slot is not included if its bit has a value of '0'.

h3ce1Type.name: h3ce1Type
h3ce1Type.description: Specifies the type of the E1 interface. Now it supports types as follow: voice voice type pos POS type

h3ce1Clock.name: h3ce1Clock
h3ce1Clock.description: Specifies the clock type used on the E1 interface.

h3ce1FrameFormat.name: h3ce1FrameFormat
h3ce1FrameFormat.description: Specifies the frame format used on the E1 interface.

h3ce1LineCode.name: h3ce1LineCode
h3ce1LineCode.description: Specifies the line code type used on the E1 interface.

h3ce1PriSetTimeSlot.name: h3ce1PriSetTimeSlot
h3ce1PriSetTimeSlot.description: This is a bit-map of PRI time slots used on the E1 interface. It needs to administratively shut down the D channel of the E1 interface before cancelling PRI time slots.

h3ce1DChannelIndex.name: h3ce1DChannelIndex
h3ce1DChannelIndex.description: This is the ifIndex of the D channel of the E1 interface.

h3ce1SubScribLineChannelIndex.name: h3ce1SubScribLineChannelIndex
h3ce1SubScribLineChannelIndex.description: This is the ifIndex of the subscriber-line channel of the E1 interface.

h3ce1FcmChannelIndex.name: h3ce1FcmChannelIndex
h3ce1FcmChannelIndex.description: This is the ifIndex of the FCM (Fast Connection Modem) channel of the E1 interface.

h3ce1InterfaceTable.name: h3ce1InterfaceTable
h3ce1InterfaceTable.description: A list of channels of E1 interface entries. Including D channels and subscriber-line channels.

h3ce1InterfaceEntry.name: h3ce1InterfaceEntry
h3ce1InterfaceEntry.description: This entry contains channels of E1 interface management information. Including D channels and subscriber-line channels.

h3ce1ControllerIndex.name: h3ce1ControllerIndex
h3ce1ControllerIndex.description: Which E1 interface is this channel belonged to.

h3ce1TimeSlotSetTable.name: h3ce1TimeSlotSetTable
h3ce1TimeSlotSetTable.description: A list of time slot set information of E1 interface entries.

h3ce1TimeSlotSetEntry.name: h3ce1TimeSlotSetEntry
h3ce1TimeSlotSetEntry.description: This entry contains time slot set information of E1 interface.

h3ce1TimeSlotSetSignalType.name: h3ce1TimeSlotSetSignalType
h3ce1TimeSlotSetSignalType.description: Signal type. Now it supports types as follow: unkown, unkown em-delay E&M Delay Dial em-immediate E&M Immediate Start em-wink E&M Wink Start fxo-ground FXO Ground Start fxo-loop FXO Loop Start fxs-ground FXS Ground Start fxs-loop FXS Loop Start r2 R2 ITU Q421
